<h2>The Future of User Experience</h2>
<p>As we move through 2024, web design continues evolving with exciting new approaches that blend aesthetics with functionality:</p>

<ul class="trend-list">
  <li>
    <strong>AI-Powered Personalization:</strong> Websites now adapt in real-time to user behavior, 
    offering customized content and layouts.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Neumorphism 2.0:</strong> The popular soft-UI design trend returns with improved 
    accessibility and performance.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Micro-Interactions:</strong> Subtle animations that guide users and make navigation 
    more intuitive.
  </li>
</ul>

<div class="stat-box">
  <h3>Did You Know?</h3>
  <p>According to 2024 research:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>53% of users will abandon a site that takes longer than 3 seconds to load</li>
    <li>Websites with proper color contrast see 42% higher engagement</li>
    <li>Mobile-first designs now account for 68% of all web traffic</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<h2>Getting Started With Modern Design</h2>
<p>To implement these trends in your projects:</p>

<ol class="steps">
  <li>Audit your current site performance using <a href="https://pagespeed.web.dev/" target="_blank">Google PageSpeed Insights</a></li>
  <li>Experiment with CSS Grid and Flexbox for responsive layouts</li>
  <li>Test your color schemes with <a href="https://coolors.co/contrast-checker" target="_blank">accessibility checkers</a></li>
</ol>

